DIGEST
SB 135 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Mizell
Present law requires that amounts collected from the tax on net gaming proceeds from sports
wagering be credited to various funds described in present law, including the La. Early
Childhood Education Fund and the Supporting Programs, Opportunities, Resources, and
Teams Fund.
Present law requires the amount credited to the La. Early Childhood Education Fund be
25%, not to exceed $20 million from the net proceeds of onsite and mobile sports wagering.
Proposed law removes the $20 million cap on amounts credited to the La. Early Childhood
Education Fund. Proposed law further requires that 25% of the net mobile sports wagering
proceeds be credited to the La. Early Childhood Education Fund.
Present law requires the amount credited to the Supporting Programs, Opportunities,
Resources, and Teams Fund be 25% of the net mobile sports wagering proceeds.
Proposed law requires a $20 million cap on the amounts credited to the Supporting
Programs, Opportunities, Resources, and Teams Fund.
Effective July 1, 2027.
(Amends R.S. 27:625(G)(2) and (8))
